{
  "texts": [
    "Throughout this manuscript, DASs were defined as the difference in power distribution between patients and the healthy cohort.",
    "For a simplified and, hopefully comprehensive, example, we kindly refer the reader to Fig.",
    "To characterize a specific DMN, all these measures were computed for each region separately and then averaged [mean ± SEM].",
    "As opposed to the Θ Richness, the DAS was computable both for DMNs and tumors since it only required two temporal series rather than a complete distribution.",
    "To compute absolute values of this score, the DAS for each region (or tumor) was made strictly positive."
  ]
}